news.title: Info Edge invests additional Rs 15 crore to increase stake in 4B Networks
news.para: The company already holds 19.9 per cent stake in 4B on a fully diluted and converted basis. The holding has now increased to 37.03 per cent.

news.title: Housing sales up 92% in July-Sep across eight top cities: Report
news.para: "The total residential sales of the top eight markets under review during Q3 2021, reached 104 per cent of 2019 quarterly average," the consultant said, adding that sales have breached pre-COVID levels.

news.title: Macrotech Developers sells properties worth Rs 1,100 crore in London
news.para: Mumbai-based Macrotech Developers, earlier named as Lodha Developers, had made a foray into the London market in 2013 with the acquisition of the landmark MacDonald House at 1 Grosvenor Square in prime Central London from the Canadian government for over GBP 300 million (Rs 3,100 crore).

news.title: Sand will be free for PMAY beneficiaries: Madhya Pradesh CM
news.para: Chief minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan said that the state government is committed for upliftment of the poor sections of society along with the all-round development of the state.

news.title: Office leasing jumps over 2.5 fold in eight cities in July-Sept: Report
news.para: The gross absorption of office space stood at 4.7 million square feet in the corresponding period of the previous year and 3.6 million square feet in the previous quarter, according to Knight Frank's India Real Estate Update - Q3 2021 that was released on Monday through a video conference.

news.title: After DHFL, Srei becomes second NBFC to be taken to bankruptcy court
news.para: DHFL was the first NBFC whose board was superseded by the Reserve Bank. Later it went through the corporate insolvency resolution process which was successfully resolved with Piramal Capital and Housing Finance Ltd acquiring the troubled housing finance company after paying creditors Rs 34,250 crore.

news.title: ED arrests Unitech's founder, daughter-in-law for financial frauds
news.para: Lookout circular was issued against her Preeti Chandra, the wife of Sanjay Chandra, Unitech promoter and son of Ramesh Chandra. Sanjay Chandra himself is behind bars on charges of money laundering.

news.title: Chandigarh Housing Board told to justify reserve price cut in writing
news.para: There are around 156 such commercial properties with the CHB having value of Rs 100 crore, according to records. All these properties are located in commercial areas of Manimajra, sectors 38 (West), 40, 49 and 51 and 61.

news.title: China Evergrande to raise $5 billion from property unit sale: Media reports
news.para: China's state-backed Global Times said Hopson Development was the buyer of a 51% stake in the property business for more than HK$40 billion ($5.1 billion), citing unspecified other media reports.

news.title: Delhi HC asks Supertech to pay Rs 40 lakh to homebuyer by Oct end
news.para: The court had on September 24, stayed an order of the National Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission (NCDRC) sentencing Supertech's MD Mohit Arora to 3-year imprisonment and issuing an arrest warrant against him for non-compliance with an order in the case by the home buyer.

news.title: Chandigarh admin objects to Rs 643 crore for 728 flats without covered area information
news.para: The covered area of any project carries multiple financial aspects. The CHB has been asked about it, so that the amount can be verified and subsequent nod given.

news.title: It is a good, bad and ugly situation in real estate, says Niranjan Hiranandani
news.para: “Positive news in terms of demand and development is taking place but K-shaped recovery means not all companies are doing very well.”

news.title: Important to have model builder-buyer agreement, says SC
news.para: "It is very important for consumer protection, because builders try to put any number of clauses in the agreement which common people may not be aware of. There should be some uniformity in the agreement. It is important that this (model builder buyer agreement) is achieved in the country," the bench said.

news.title: SC dismisses Supertech's plea seeking modification of order to raze twin towers
news.para: In its application, Supertech Ltd has said that due to the proximity of Tower-17 (Ceyane) with the other residential towers in its Emerald Court project, it cannot demolish the building by blowing through explosives and it would have to be done brick by brick.

news.title: Four greenfield airports may be ready in 3-4 years in Karnataka
news.para: While nearly 45 per cnt of the Shivamogga airport work is over, the land acquisition process has been completed for Hassan and Raichur.
